2601.definition: [καταβιβάζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of the base of {{G939}}; to cause to go down, i.e. precipitate

2602.definition: [καταβολή] from {{G2598}}; a deposition, i.e. founding; figuratively, conception

2603.definition: [καταβραβεύω] from {{G2596}} and {{G1018}} (in its original sense); to award the price against, i.e. (figuratively) to defraud (of salvation)

2605.definition: [καταγγέλλω] from {{G2596}} and the base of {{G32}}; to proclaim, promulgate

2607.definition: [καταγινώσκω] from {{G2596}} and {{G1097}}; to note against, i.e. find fault with

2608.definition: [κατάγνυμι] from {{G2596}} and the base of {{G4486}}; to rend in pieces, i.e. crack apart

2609.definition: [κατάγω] from {{G2596}} and {{G71}}; to lead down; specially, to moor a vessel

2610.definition: [καταγωνίζομαι] from {{G2596}} and {{G75}}; to struggle against, i.e. (by implication) to overcome

2611.definition: [καταδέω] from {{G2596}} and {{G1210}}; to tie down, i.e. bandage (a wound)

2613.definition: [καταδικάζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G1349}}; to adjudge against, i.e. pronounce guilty

2614.definition: [καταδιώκω] from {{G2596}} and {{G1377}}; to hunt down, i.e. search for

2616.definition: [καταδυναστεύω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G1413}}; to exercise dominion against, i.e. oppress

2617.definition: [καταισχύνω] from {{G2596}} and {{G153}}; to shame down, i.e. disgrace or (by implication) put to the blush

2618.definition: [κατακαίω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2545}}; to burn down (to the ground), i.e. consume wholly

2619.definition: [κατακαλύπτω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2572}}; to cover wholly, i.e. veil

2620.definition: [κατακαυχάομαι] from {{G2596}} and {{G2744}}; to exult against (i.e. over)

2621.definition: [κατάκειμαι] from {{G2596}} and {{G2749}}; to lie down, i.e. (by implication) be sick; specially, to recline at a meal

2622.definition: [κατακλάω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2806}}; to break down, i.e. divide

2623.definition: [κατακλείω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2808}}; to shut down (in a dungeon), i.e. incarcerate

2624.definition: [κατακληροδοτέω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of a compound of {{G2819}} and {{G1325}}; to be a giver of lots to each, i.e. (by implication) to apportion an estate

2625.definition: [κατακλίνω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2827}}; to recline down, i.e. (specially) to take a place at table

2626.definition: [κατακλύζω] from {{G2596}} and the base of {{G2830}}; to dash (wash) down, i.e. (by implication) to deluge

2629.definition: [κατακόπτω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2875}}; to chop down, i.e. mangle

2630.definition: [κατακρημνίζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G2911}}; to precipitate down

2632.definition: [κατακρίνω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2919}}; to judge against, i.e. sentence

2634.definition: [κατακυριεύω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2961}}; to lord against, i.e. control, subjugate

2635.definition: [καταλαλέω] from {{G2637}}; to be a traducer, i.e. to slander

2637.definition: [κατάλαλος] from {{G2596}} and the base of {{G2980}}; talkative against, i.e. a slanderer

2638.definition: [καταλαμβάνω] from {{G2596}} and {{G2983}}; to take eagerly, i.e. seize, possess, etc. (literally or figuratively)

2639.definition: [καταλέγω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3004}} (in its original meaning); to lay down, i.e. (figuratively) to enrol

2640.definition: [κατάλειμμα] from {{G2641}}; a remainder, i.e. (by implication) a few

2641.definition: [καταλείπω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3007}}; to leave down, i.e. behind; by implication, to abandon, have remaining

2642.definition: [καταλιθάζω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3034}}; to stone down, i.e. to death

2643.definition: [καταλλαγή] from {{G2644}}; exchange (figuratively, adjustment), i.e. restoration to (the divine) favor

2644.definition: [καταλλάσσω] from {{G2596}} and {{G236}}; to change mutually, i.e. (figuratively) to compound a difference

2645.definition: [κατάλοιπος] from {{G2596}} and {{G3062}}; left down (behind), i.e remaining (plural the rest)

2646.definition: [κατάλυμα] from {{G2647}}; properly, a dissolution (breaking up of a journey), i.e. (by implication) a lodging-place

2647.definition: [καταλύω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3089}}; to loosen down (disintegrate), i.e. (by implication) to demolish (literally or figuratively); specially (compare {{G2646}}) to halt for the night

2648.definition: [καταμανθάνω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3129}}; to learn thoroughly, i.e. (by implication) to note carefully

2650.definition: [καταμένω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3306}}; to stay fully, i.e. reside

2651.definition: [καταμόνας] from {{G2596}} and accusative case plural feminine of {{G3441}} (with {{G5561}} implied); according to sole places, i.e. (adverbially) separately

2655.definition: [καταναρκάω] from {{G2596}} and ναρκάω (to be numb); to grow utterly torpid, i.e. (by implication) slothful (figuratively, expensive)

2656.definition: [κατανεύω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3506}}; to nod down (towards), i.e. (by analogy) to make signs to

2658.definition: [καταντάω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G473}}; to meet against, i.e. arrive at (literally or figuratively)

2659.definition: [κατάνυξις] from {{G2660}}; a prickling (sensation, as of the limbs asleep), i.e. (by implication, (perhaps by some confusion with {{G3506}} or even with {{G3571}})) stupor (lethargy)

2660.definition: [κατανύσσω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3572}}; to pierce thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) to agitate violently ("sting to the quick")

2661.definition: [καταξιόω] from {{G2596}} and {{G515}}; to deem entirely deserving

2662.definition: [καταπατέω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3961}}; to trample down; figuratively, to reject with disdain

2663.definition: [κατάπαυσις] from {{G2664}}; reposing down, i.e. (by Hebraism) abode

2664.definition: [καταπαύω] from {{G2596}} and {{G3973}}; to settle down, i.e. (literally) to colonize, or (figuratively) to (cause to) desist

2665.definition: [καταπέτασμα] from a compound of {{G2596}} and a congener of {{G4072}}; something spread thoroughly, i.e. (specially) the door screen (to the Most Holy Place) in the Jewish Temple

2666.definition: [καταπίνω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4095}}; to drink down, i.e. gulp entire (literally or figuratively)

2668.definition: [καταπλέω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4126}}; to sail down upon a place, i.e. to land at

2669.definition: [καταπονέω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G4192}}; to labor down, i.e. wear with toil (figuratively, harass)

2670.definition: [καταποντίζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of the same as {{G4195}}; to plunge down, i.e. submerge

2672.definition: [καταράομαι] middle voice from {{G2671}}; to execrate; by analogy, to doom

2673.definition: [καταργέω] from {{G2596}} and {{G691}}; to be (render) entirely idle (useless), literally or figuratively

2675.definition: [καταρτίζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G739}}; to complete thoroughly, i.e. repair (literally or figuratively) or adjust

2678.definition: [κατασείω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4579}}; to sway downward, i.e. make a signal

2679.definition: [κατασκάπτω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4626}}; to undermine, i.e. (by implication) destroy

2680.definition: [κατασκευάζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G4632}}; to prepare thoroughly (properly, by external equipment; whereas {{G2090}} refers rather to internal fitness); by implication, to construct, create

2681.definition: [κατασκηνόω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4637}}; to camp down, i.e. haunt; figuratively, to remain

2682.definition: [κατασκήνωσις] from {{G2681}}; an encamping, i.e. (figuratively) a perch

2683.definition: [κατασκιάζω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G4639}}; to overshade, i.e. cover

2684.definition: [κατασκοπέω] from {{G2685}}; to be a sentinel, i.e. to inspect insidiously

2685.definition: [κατάσκοπος] from {{G2596}} (intensive) and {{G4649}} (in the sense of a watcher); a reconnoiterer

2686.definition: [κατασοφίζομαι] middle voice from {{G2596}} and {{G4679}}; to be crafty against, i.e. circumvent

2687.definition: [καταστέλλω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4724}}; to put down, i.e. quell

2688.definition: [κατάστημα] from {{G2525}}; properly, a position or condition, i.e. (subjectively) demeanor

2690.definition: [καταστρέφω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4762}}; to turn upside down, i.e. upset

2691.definition: [καταστρηνιάω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4763}}; to become voluptuous against

2692.definition: [καταστροφή] from {{G2690}}; an overturn ("catastrophe"), i.e. demolition; figuratively, apostasy

2693.definition: [καταστρώννυμι] from {{G2596}} and {{G4766}}; to strew down, i.e. (by implication) to prostrate (slay)

2694.definition: [κατασύρω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4951}}; to drag down, i.e. arrest judicially

2695.definition: [κατασφάττω] from {{G2596}} and {{G4969}}; to kill down, i.e. slaughter

2697.definition: [κατάσχεσις] from {{G2722}}; a holding down, i.e. occupancy

2698.definition: [κατατίθημι] from {{G2596}} and {{G5087}}; to place down, i.e. deposit (literally or figuratively)

2699.definition: [κατατομή] from a compound of {{G2596}} and τέμνω (to cut); a cutting down (off), i.e. mutilation (ironically) Compare {{G609}}.

2700.definition: [κατατοξεύω] from {{G2596}} and a derivative of {{G5115}}; to shoot down with an arrow or other missile
